On Mon, 24 Mar 2003 willisbsmooth(-at-)msn.com wrote:

> Just wire it to the fuse panel up front
> ground it, and put a switch on or under the dash to the ground wire
> I wired a bilge blower fan in my main heater channel that way.
> the switch was purchased at the marine store where i got the fan.
> good luck

I use the air conditioner blower in much the same fashion, mounted the
switch on a plug over the ash tray opening, since I don't smoke I removed
it and made an accesory panel to fit there, will hold 3 switches

